Firestarter GUI for advanced Firewall:

http://www.tecmint.com/firestarter-a-high-level-graphical-interface-iptables-firewall-for-linux-systems/
http://www.fs-security.com/

How to instal and setup:

On RHEL/CentOS/Fedora
Firestarter packages available in RPM package format for your RPM based Linux distributions like Red Hat, CentOS and Fedora. 
Therefore, download the latest stable RPM package specific to your distribution using below link.

	http://www.fs-security.com/download.php

Once, youâ€™ve downloaded the package, open a terminal and change to the directory where you downloaded the RPM and type the following command to install the package.

	# rpm -Uvh firestarter*rpm

Compiling and Installing from Source
First, download the tar.gz version using the wget command. 
Unpack the tarball using tar command and move into the newly created directory and then configure, compile and install it as shown below.

	# wget http://kaz.dl.sourceforge.net/project/firestarter/firestarter/1.0.3/firestarter-1.0.3.tar.gz
	# tar -xvf firestarter-1.0.3.tar.gz
	# cd firestarter-1.0.3
	# ./configure --sysconfdir=/etc
	# make
	# make install


